variables.name: CONNECTION_PRIMARY_SERVING
variables.comment: * UE has connection to cell for signalling and possibly data (3GPP 36.331, 25.331).

variables.name: CONNECTION_SECONDARY_SERVING
variables.comment: * UE has connection to cell for data (3GPP 36.331, 25.331).

variables.name: mCellConnectionStatus
variables.comment:
* Connection status of the cell. * *

One of {@link #CONNECTION_PRIMARY_SERVING}, {@link #CONNECTION_SECONDARY_SERVING}.

variables.name: mRat
variables.comment: * The radio technology for this physical channel.

variables.name: mFrequencyRange
variables.comment: * The rough frequency range for this physical channel.

variables.name: mChannelNumber
variables.comment: * The absolute radio frequency channel number, {@link Integer#MAX_VALUE} if unknown.

variables.name: mContextIds
variables.comment:
* A list of data calls mapped to this physical channel. An empty list means the physical
     * channel has no data call mapped to it.

variables.name: mPhysicalCellId
variables.comment: * The physical cell identifier for this cell - PCI, PSC, {@link Integer#MAX_VALUE} if known.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(Parcel dest, int flags)
public int[] getContextIds()
methods.comment:
* Get the list of data call ids mapped to this physical channel. This list is sorted into
     * ascending numerical order. Each id in this list must match the id in
     * {@link com.android.internal.telephony.dataconnection.DataConnection}. An empty list means the
     * physical channel has no data call mapped to it.
     *
     * @return an integer list indicates the data call ids.

methods.name: public int getFrequencyRange()
public int getChannelNumber()
methods.comment:
* @return the absolute radio frequency channel number for this physical channel,
     * {@link Integer#MAX_VALUE} if unknown.

methods.name: public int getPhysicalCellId()
methods.comment:
* In UTRAN, this value is primary scrambling code. The range is [0, 511].
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 25.213 section 5.2.2.
     *
     * In EUTRAN, this value is physical layer cell identity. The range is [0, 503].
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 36.211 section 6.11.
     *
     * In 5G RAN, this value is physical layer cell identity. The range is [0, 1008].
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 38.211 section 7.4.2.1.
     *
     * @return the physical cell identifier for this cell, {@link Integer#MAX_VALUE} if unknown.

methods.name: public int getRat()
methods.comment: The radio technology for this physical channel.

methods.name: public int getConnectionStatus()
methods.comment:
* Gets the connection status of the cell.
     *
     * @see #CONNECTION_PRIMARY_SERVING
     * @see #CONNECTION_SECONDARY_SERVING
     * @see #CONNECTION_UNKNOWN
     *
     * @return Connection status of the cell

methods.name: private String getConnectionStatusString()
methods.comment: @return String representation of the connection status
